race.comment: SQUEEZEBOX (2) opened this prep well enough but was very one-paced last start over this trip at Kembla. Would normally be concerned with him staying at 1500m but the blinkers are back on today which should sharpen him up. Worth another chance. BLUEBIRD BAY (1) returned from a 24-week spell last time out and was having his first run for the new stable when a closing fourth over 1300m at Scone. Beaten under a length at Newcastle at the same stage last prep. Hard to hold out over the extra furlong. MISS HVAR (3) has settled back in the field and failed to threaten in her two runs this prep. Lightly raced mare who gets a gear change today and strips fitter so can improve sharply. GWENDIE (4) struggled at the end of 2000m last start. Placed two from three at this distance so can make amends. OH DEER (5) dominated first-up at Tuncurry and should have a lot more to offer.
